spans.text: find What all must confess to be rare
What all must confess to be rare
clusters appear more transparent and fine
the vapours that rise from the earth in the morn
clear all the hues of the leaves
reaping the wheat , others binding the sheaves
the fish on the hook Struggles hard to procure its release
the long wished for time of their meeting
claps the poor jades on the neck
all the pleasure retirement affords , Still amused with these innocent sports , Nor once envy the pomp of fine ladies and lords
the pomp of fine ladies and lords
the pomp of fine ladies and lords
has force to control , And unite all the passions in love
In the farm , or the village hard by
